Edo state Governor Godwin Obaseki has mourned the death of Chief Oyuki Jackson Obaseki who died at the weekend in Benin City, the Edo State capital, at the age of 75. In a statement, Special Adviser to the Governor on Media and Communication Strategy, Crusoe Osagie, quoted the governor as saying: “Chief Oyuki’s passing is a personal loss to me. He was a very generous leader who took delight in sharing his knowledge and experience for the good of society.“I pray that the Almighty God grants his soul repose until we meet to part no more on resurrection morning.” To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .